items.name: Psychedelic Rooms - [Topnotch Artstyle]
items.description:
Trained with Dreambooth (JP's repo local) on ~20 images of "psychedelic rooms" generated by Midjourney V5.

As the name implies this model defaults to generating rooms in a home mostly. If you enter the trigger words "Topnotch Artstyle" SD will generate an image of a room in this style. That said, it works well in lots of other instances - just play around w/ prompts.

The model was trained on SD V1.5 so it works well with that checkpoint. It looks really good to me with RealisticVision - anything based on SD 1.5 should work to a degree.

I have a ton of random "topnotch" checkpoints I've created over the past 8months w/ Dreambooth. I've just learned how to extract them to LoRA so I may toss some others out under the same "Topnotch Artstyle" name. I'll see how this one goes.

Enjoy!

items.name: JTVeemo - Artist Style (LoRA/Lycoris)
items.description:
If you enjoyed this model, why don't you check out my other works? I put a lot of effort into correctly recreating artist styles and making the occasional character LoRA.üòä

This model was trained using the collab/guide by holostrawberry [Guide] Make your own Loras, easy and free - colabs | Stable Diffusion Other | Civitai

There already exist other LoRAs for this style on civitai and huggingface that tend to be heavily overbaked or were trained for some other checkpoints. Check the recommendation below.

About the artist:

Pixiv Fanbox: „Éì„É¢ÔΩúpixivFANBOX

Twitter: „Éì„É¢üêôü¶ë (@JT_Veemo) / Twitter

Patreon: JTveemo | Creating cute stuff and NSFW | Patreon

JTVeemo is in large part a hentai artist. They are mostly known for making horny fanart of Splatoon and other videogame characters (Pokemon, Zelda and Genshin just to name a few).

Most characteristic are the eyes and a general softness/thickness in design.

Weights & Prompts

Note that these models work particularly well for NSFW images. For inspiration check the examples.

The only necessary prompt is:

jtveemo

LoCon (NAI):

This is the goto version for most checkpoints. Unlike the first two versions it was trained and tested on NAI and has far more vibrant colors.

Use a weight of 0.7-1.0, adjust to taste and depending on your checkpoint.

Note, that the resemblance also scales with the number of sampling steps used.

Beware the occassional inklings, which tend to be tied to specific prompts like gradient hair.

More sampling steps or additional negative prompts can prevent that.

AOM3 Lycoris:

This version was specifically trained on Abyss Orange Mix 3. It is (hopefully) the final and definitive version, as it exceeds the others in flexibility and accuracy.

Use a weight of 1.0, adjust to taste. This model is really flexible and is compatible with other LoRA (character or pose models) at full weight. As usual I have included an XYZ plot for reference.

LoRA:

I recommend a weight around 0.7 which is compatible with most character lora. You can go higher if this is the only lora used.

Lycoris:

Use a weight of around 1.0, whether you use other LoRA or not. Adjust to taste.

The Lycoris model is a bit weaker than the LoRA but that makes it more flexible.

Please leave a review if you enjoyed this model or have problems with it. This helps me with improving future models and finetuning them in general. Give it a try and throw some images down below! üëá

items.name: bimbostyleFourUSD (SD_v1.5)
items.description:
This is model uses the exact same input as bimbostyleFour and bimbostyleFourU.

I was trained on SD_v1.5 which hopefully means that it's better applicable to other .ckpt in comparison to the normal "bimbostyleFour" and will trsy to emulate the style of the ckpt more than the deliberateV2 one

This lora is very responsive to body size prompts i.e. large breasts/wide hips/thick lips

And can also be used to bimbofie an existing model or lora

Combining this Lora together with One/Two/Three/Four in a "draw style" ckpt give great results and i can only recommend trying it out. (i don't know if the same applies to "real" ones as well)

can be mixed with every other bimbostyle

If you mix my models, i would recommend to always put the stronger weighted Lora in the front. i.e.

<lora:bimbostyleThree:0.5>:<lora:bimbostyleTwo:0.3>

Also i would go above a combined strength of 1 and from experience i would say .75-.9 is the sweet spot total strength

items.name: Mystique
items.description:
Trained on 14 images (art, cosplay, and movie stills). She's got the textured skin of the live action version. It can get a little over-zealous sometimes, but is manageable. Doesn't need clothes, but occasionally decides to wear a belt, and likes white dresses.

Examples are cherry picked from a batch x/y/z plot of various styles and checkpoints using a single random seed. No post processing of any kind (eg - inpainting, photoshop, restore face..) Xformers was enabled, so your image may differ slightly.

Weight: 0.7-1

During the week, I plan to do an updated model on fewer images to make the clothes and hair more controllable (293 images is an obvious overkill). Because now more than 2/3 of the entire dataset is in hiking clothes and 90% with a pink bow. Also, I will most likely split into 2 models, one for the first year and one for school with a traveling.

Based on a fantasy adventure slice of life light novel series written by Chirolu and illustrated by Truffle (Vol.1) and Kei (Vol.2 - ).

Dale is a cool, composed, and highly skilled adventurer who's made quite a name for himself despite his youth. One day on a job deep in the forest, he comes across a little devil girl who's almost wasted away. Unable to just leave her there to die, Dale takes her home and becomes her adoptive father. Devil or not, Latina is beyond adorable, and the adventurer soon finds himself head over heels with being a parent. But why was she out in the forest to begin with, and why does she carry the mark of a criminal?

items.name: Saya | Saya no uta Character LoRA
items.description:
Recommended weight 0.65-0.95. Interesting results with more weight, but more artifacts.

Sometimes there are problems with generating hair flaps and white sandals, solved by increasing the weights and reroll.

My first lora, so it's not ideal at all. It was noticed that sometimes one image from a dataset can be used too often. I haven't tried it with other loras, but I don't think the result will be bad.

Triggers: saya, saya no uta, hair flaps.
Maybe in the future I'll add images from the visual novel for the official artstyle.
Trained on Anything v4.5

---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
V2!
In this version I adjusted captions via wd captions, which is why I strongly recommend to use v2 and not v1. I added support for visual novel style via official artstyle, official art, game cg tags. Also try nsfw (included in dataset), eldritch abomination, wings.

items.name: Sandstone Weathered Texture
items.description:
Weathered sandstone LoRA, created from an in-house photo dataset of textures. The LoRA is intended to use as a texture creation helper and works in scenes to texture objects. The goal was to create a set of LoRAs to add randomness and structure usable for various textured photos. Works also well for tileable texture creation. 768x768 (SDXL 1024x1024). Try to use weights 0.4-1 or higher for more detail of texture.

For tutorials and guides on generative AI applications in art, graphic design, 3D and AR/VR, check my website sandner.art in section https://sandner.art/articles/ai/

You can support my adventures by buying me a coffee: https://ko-fi.com/airesearch

Have fun rendering!

items.name: CoalMix
items.description:
Pushing the brinks of semi realism. With insane clarity in images, better faces, extremely detailed backgrounds and more with CoalMix.

NOTE: ALL IMAGES SHOULD BE MADE WITH EASY NEGATVIE AND BAD PROMPT V2 ALL LINKS HERE: https://huggingface.co/datasets/gsdf/EasyNegative/blob/main/EasyNegative.pt

https://huggingface.co/datasets/Nerfgun3/bad_prompt/blob/main/bad_prompt_version2.pt

Hello people. Today I have yet another insane mix for you guys today.

CoalMix.

A semi-realistic anime mix that would take hours just to tell you guys the mix. So I won't. But I got that nice stuff for you guys today. A very good model that is probably the most realistic one yet, here is the recommended settings.

Steps: Test: 20-30. Illustration 30-150.

CFG Scale: 5+, 5 for simple prompts, 10 for advanced and long prompts. Twelve for huge prompts.

Sampler: Euler A or DPM ++SDE Karras.

Upscaler: Your pick.

Lastly, this model is very good even on 20 steps. It can create very good images, not to mention the clarity of the backgrounds of the images. In fact I ran tests on my friends on some of the images and they never even knew they were AI. This model is that good.

items.name: VRChat Furries v3 (for Yiffymix 2.1)
items.description:
VRChat Furries

New version : V3.1 and V3.2

  • v3.1 is sometimes a bit more artistic than v3.2 but v3.2 has much better anatomy

  • better style

  • better clothes and muscles anatomy

  • new "swaggy" keyword that makes everything looks more fresh and cool ^^

Trained for the Yiffymix v2.1 model (https://civitai.com/models/3671?modelVersionId=65078)

YOU NEED TO REDUCE THE STRENGTH OF THE MODEL TO <0.8

+ Work better with CFG Scale between 2 and 3

+ USE SPECIFIC VERSIONS if you want to avoid species blend

+ Use clip skip 2

Contains :

  • Rexouium (keyword: rexouium)

  • Avali with kitavali and davali (keywords: avali, kitavali or avali, davali)

  • Nardoragon (keyword: nardo)

  • Deuzear (keyword: deuzear)

  • Wickerbeast (keyword: wickerbeast)

  • Protogen (keyword: protogen)

Also works well with anime boy and anime girl

Styles (keywords) :

  • comic

  • thick lines

  • photography

  • render

  • painting

  • swaggy

  • draft

Composition (keywords) :

  • rim light

  • good lights

  • good composition

  • dynamic scene

  • complex scene

  • bicolor

  • monocolor

Anatomy (keywords) :

  • cute

  • teenager

  • (very / extremely, slightly / - ) muscular

  • ripped muscles

  • (spiky / wavy / feather) hairs

Clothes (keywords) :

  • (tight / - ) shirt

  • short

  • legging

  • hoodie

  • bandana

Position (keywords)

  • dynamic position

  • seated

  • lying

  • crouching

  • looking down

  • side view

  • 3/4 view, three-quarter view

  • back view

Discord server to see or share other generated images : https://discord.gg/bC6U4GwbAt

If you have any questions or suggestion don't hesitate to contact me on discord blackorbit#6018

Works very well with :

  • Gacha splash LORA painting style + epic background and arrangements + improves anatomy (biased towards shorts + thinner body) https://civitai.com/models/13090?modelVersionId=26536

  • BulkedUp AI forces fit / muscular (ultra biased towards standing strait + needs to reduce the strength of this lora model) https://civitai.com/models/26303/bulkedup-ai-huge-muscles-lora --> don't need anymore with new version

  • Eonn makes everything more colorful (conflict with muscles / anatomy sometimes) https://civitai.com/models/6016/neon-diffusion

Tips & tricks :

  • improve avali look by adding those keywords : cute, big eyes, feathers, black eyes

  • get better faces by adding those keywords : close up portrait

  • profile or side view key words : side view

  • sometimes can get better faces by changing hairs / furs colors

  • you can choose rexouium hairs (keywords: spiky hairs, wavy hairs, feather hairs)

  • seems like the rexouium keyword is a bit overtrained on the v2.1, you can use (rexouium:0.7) to make it less deep fried looking

Planned for next version (V4):

  • better support of blurry background

  • better tail control (on/off)

  • fat keyword ?

  • reference sheet ?

  • new species ? (awter, taidum, )

Kim Se-jeong (ÍπÄÏÑ∏Ï†ï)

Kim Se-Jeong is a South Korean singer and actress. This LoRA is trained on 19 images in 1900 steps. The reccomended settings are:

Sampling method - DPM++ SDE Keras

Sampling steps - 35-50

CFG scale - 7

LoRA weight - 1

items.name: Erik Johansson Style
items.description:
Erik Johansson is a Swedish photographer and visual artist known for his mind-bending and surreal photographic artworks. He is celebrated for his mastery of digital manipulation, seamlessly blending various elements to create captivating and otherworldly compositions.

Johansson's photography often begins with capturing multiple photographs of different elements and landscapes. He then meticulously combines these images using digital editing techniques, resulting in fantastical scenes that challenge the viewer's perception of reality.

His artwork frequently revolves around impossible and surreal scenarios, such as floating islands, upside-down landscapes, or buildings merging with nature. Johansson's meticulous attention to detail and technical expertise allow him to create seamless visual illusions that appear both fantastical and believable.

Beyond his technical prowess, Johansson's work carries conceptual depth and often addresses social and environmental themes. He uses his art as a means of storytelling, raising questions, and evoking emotions in viewers.

Johansson's artworks have gained international recognition and have been featured in exhibitions, galleries, and publications worldwide. He has collaborated with various clients, including advertising agencies and renowned brands, to create visually stunning and thought-provoking campaigns.

Erik Johansson's photography is characterized by its imaginative and surreal nature, combining technical expertise with conceptual storytelling. His ability to transform ordinary scenes into extraordinary visual experiences has made him a prominent figure in the world of digital art and photography. His artworks challenge our perception, ignite our imagination, and invite us into a world where the boundaries of reality and possibility are pushed to their limits.

items.name: Photoreal District 9 Aliens
items.description:
| District 9 Photoreal |

What is it?

Superdetailed-grungy-LoRA trained on high quality scanned photographs of the alien puppets/props sculpted and made for District 9. On the surface it might seem like a one-off Lora but this one packs so much detail and grit it will give many other render-themes a push forward! Also, an amazing thank you to the hard working people that built these for the movie, incredible artistry - mainly WƒìtƒÅ FX in collaboration with Image Engine VFX!

I'd love to see some generations you come up with!

How to use it?

The Lora reacts on the keyword "alien", "District 9" and "OliDistrict". It was trained on verticals torso, but also legs and body - it is a bit weak and it needs to be pushed in that direction in the prompt!

Some images are using my other LoRA in the mix: Soul of Disco - Disco Diffusion Lora

P.S All the PNGs have data on them! The model is a custom model merged with others and I might or might not release it, but I don't know yet.

First of all, trained on sd 1.5, around 1500 steps. You can use it on any checkpoint related to 1.5, works fine with the less realistic ones too.

Second of all, I recommend not using the restore faces option with this lora, the results are (imo) a bit better without it. I think 4 of the 5 images I added are without restore faces. Values between 0.4 and 0.7.

Third of all, this was a bit of a pain to get quite right, it is still not perfect (rigid poses, some skin inconsistencies) and I will return to this later, but part of it can be fixed with prompts/inpaint/img2img.

Fourth and last, if you like it, would appreciate a like :-)

Heck's photography is characterized by its vibrant and bold use of color, intricate compositions, and a dreamlike quality. He often incorporates elements of painting, graphic design, and surrealism into his images, creating a visual language that is both captivating and ethereal.

His fashion photography goes beyond mere representation of clothing and models, transcending into the realm of art. Heck's images often feature elaborate sets, rich textures, and intricate patterns, creating a visual feast for the eyes. He pays meticulous attention to detail and carefully orchestrates every element within the frame to create a harmonious and visually arresting composition.

In addition to his fashion work, Heck has also created fine art photography series that explore various themes and subjects. His fine art images often convey a sense of introspection, emotion, and narrative, blurring the line between reality and imagination.

Heck's distinctive style has garnered him recognition and acclaim in the photography world. His work has been featured in prestigious publications, exhibited in galleries and museums worldwide, and he has collaborated with renowned fashion brands and designers.

Erik Madigan Heck's photography pushes the boundaries of traditional fashion photography, creating a unique and visionary body of work that merges the realms of fashion and fine art. His use of color, composition, and meticulous attention to detail set him apart, resulting in visually stunning and thought-provoking imagery.

items.name: Based66
items.description:
CC License

The next installment in my Based mixes, Based66 aims to have better LORA compatibility while maintaining the more sharper lines/softer color Anime appearance I wanted with the future installment of my models. This model was mostly made with the desire to circumvent the troubles Based65 had with LORA compatibility due to too many finetuned models which I was unaware of in the mix, so in Based66 the only finetuned model I made sure to use in the mix was HLL4, the 4th installment of the Vtuber finetuned model which I was using the 3rd version in Based64 and Based65. The 4th version of the Vtuber finetune is here like always. (B66 was also made to get into the current rise of mixes being posted online, despite B64 and B65 being uploaded to my Civitai page not too long ago those models were made way long before so B66 is the actual "new player" I decided to introduce into the current meta for more recent model mixes)

Based66 was made with a bigger focus on MBW and presets, I made sure to focus on specific seeds and the x/y grid option provided by the Supermerger to ensure specific issues were solved and avoided with earlier iterations of the model which were lost to the void (aside from the official first version of the model that I uploaded to huggingface, the only issue with that model was anatomy and some weird lighting issues but it was fixed with version 2) however those fixes lead to some good and some bad of the model which I will try fixing in the future for version 3, which currently they aren't as big of an issue like the issues with version 1 but I'll explain the good quirks and bad quirks about this model

Usage

I was testing the max steps I'm fine with 40 with CFG scale 10 with some example outputs and it works fine but you can just keep to the trusty 7 CFG scale and 20-25 steps I usually use but otherwise the most important thing to know about this model is that it's not VAE baked, so there's no VAE in this model because I prefer all models make me pick my own VAE in the stable diffusion settings so use kl-f8-anime2 by Hakurei, it looks a lot nicer in B66 avoided that super orange tint that I didn't like with B64, otherwise that's all you have to know about using this model, it works like any other Anime mix so just use it as you please, but now we get into the specific issues I saw with V2 I saw with some earlier testers

V2 needs stronger weights (1.x) with specific prompts to have the model listen to it

V2 is too faithful to LORAs leading to the need for stronger weights with specific prompts to have the model output it correctly

V2 has trouble with multiple LORAs (eg: concept/character/style) I will be working on V3 right away to fix this issue

these are all issues I will fix in V3 however V2 being too faithful to LORAs is something I desired but at a cost, B65 had trouble with LORAs so my goal with B66 was to have it listen/understand LORAs for outputs a lot more better which it did however this issue is not as huge as the issues I saw testers have with V1, so I'm fine with this issue for now until I put effort into seeing what can fix that for version 3.

Which all major issues with V2 have been fixed with the V3 upload so you can use up to 3 LORAs and there's no need for stronger weights to get the desired output especially when using LORAs compared to V2

Future Notes

V3 may be the final version of this model before I proceed to Based67, for now I'm satisfied with the major issues I have fixed but if you're looking for the unpruned versions of Based66 just go onto my huggingface page to find them all

Support

Pretty sure a lot of model mixers have wrote that they would love it if you support them in anyway to links that they provide given that model mixing does take a long time (not as long thanks to supermerger but still does take a lot of time out of the day to get the right outputs) and you can do that for me, I would just be happy if you support me by looking at my Pixiv or Twitter for any outputs I make with my mixes and LORAs I train (which I will be going back to since I need to get back into the LORA meta) but if you wish to support me financially which would help me out in a lot of ways please do, I have the basic sites that most people use for donations like Ko-Fi and whatever but I also have services available for anyone that has stuff they want me to do work on, you can see all of them on my Linktree! Most of all just have a great time with B66 and ensure you have fun while using it (because at this rate I feel like I'm done with B66 and will move onto B67) that's the biggest support you can do for me! Until then, I'll go back to LORA baking and focus my efforts on there until I have time to pour into making version 3 of this model that fixes the need for stronger weights on prompts.
